modules.description: This module defines and manipulates property descriptors used to structure dynamic page data in Inertia.js responses. It provides operations to create, inspect, and resolve properties, including handling merge and loading modes. These properties are used to build and serialize component-specific data for Inertia page renders.

This module defines a template rendering system for Inertia.js responses in a Dream web application. It works with `page_data` to generate HTML output using a provided renderer function. Concrete use cases include constructing and rendering full HTML pages with dynamic content for Inertia-driven client-side navigation.

This module handles Inertia.js requests in a Dream web application with middleware for request processing, property management, and response rendering. It works with Dream's middleware stack, request/response types, and property descriptors to manage dynamic page data and client-side navigation. Concrete use cases include rendering Inertia pages with dynamic props, deferring property resolution, and redirecting Inertia requests with encrypted history.
